definitions: To move gently to and fro or from side to side.
To cause to sway or move back and forth.
To be full of a specified quality or thing.
To perform or play rock music.
To be very successful or impressive.
examples: The boat began to rock in the waves.
She rocked the baby to sleep.
The party was rocking all night.
The band will rock the stadium.
He really knows how to rock a suit.
